<p>Global Ecological Footprint and biocapacity metrics are calculated each year in the National Footprint and Biocapacity Accounts, based on United Nations or UN affiliated data sets. </p>

<p>Using UN statistics, these accounts incorporate the latest data and the most updated accounting methodology. </p>

<p>To maintain consistency with the latest reported data and science, the ecological footprint metrics for past years are recalculated every year.</p>

<p>The dates of past Earth Overshoot Days, recalculated with the National Footprint and Biocapacity Accounts 2019 Edition, are on the Earth Overshoot Day's website. </p>
